sequenceDiagram
    participant MLApp as ML Application
    participant Route as OpenShift Route<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant OnlineSvc as feast-online Service<br/>80 or 443/TCP
    participant FeatureServer as Feature Server Pod<br/>6566/TCP HTTP/gRPC
    participant Registry as Registry<br/>(local/S3/remote)
    participant OnlineStore as Online Store<br/>(Redis/DynamoDB/SQLite)
    participant TransformSvc as Transformation Service<br/>gRPC

    Note over MLApp,TransformSvc: Flow 1: Online Feature Retrieval

    MLApp->>Route: POST /get-online-features<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS
    Route->>OnlineSvc: Forward (re-encrypt TLS)
    OnlineSvc->>FeatureServer: HTTP/6566<br/>OIDC/K8s RBAC Auth
    FeatureServer->>Registry: Load feature definitions<br/>File/HTTPS, Optional TLS
    Registry-->>FeatureServer: Feature metadata
    FeatureServer->>OnlineStore: Fetch feature values<br/>TCP/6379 or HTTPS/443<br/>Password/IAM Auth
    OnlineStore-->>FeatureServer: Feature values
    opt On-Demand Feature Views (ODFV)
        FeatureServer->>TransformSvc: Transform request<br/>gRPC (insecure)
        TransformSvc-->>FeatureServer: Transformed features
    end
    FeatureServer-->>OnlineSvc: JSON/Proto response
    OnlineSvc-->>Route: Response
    Route-->>MLApp: Feature values

    Note over MLApp,TransformSvc: Flow 2: Feature Materialization via CronJob

    participant CronJob as CronJob Pod<br/>(origin-cli image)
    participant OfflineStore as Offline Store<br/>(PostgreSQL/Snowflake)

    CronJob->>FeatureServer: kubectl exec<br/>feast materialize-incremental<br/>In-cluster TLS, SA Token
    FeatureServer->>OfflineStore: Read historical features<br/>TCP (varies), Optional TLS
    OfflineStore-->>FeatureServer: Feature data
    FeatureServer->>OnlineStore: Write materialized features<br/>TCP (varies), Optional TLS
    OnlineStore-->>FeatureServer: Write confirmation

    Note over MLApp,TransformSvc: Flow 3: FeatureStore CR Reconciliation

    participant User as Data Scientist
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Operator as Feast Operator

    User->>K8sAPI: Create/Update FeatureStore CR
    K8sAPI->>Operator: Watch notification
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Deployment<br/>HTTPS/6443, SA Token
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Services<br/>HTTPS/6443, SA Token
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create ConfigMaps, PVCs<br/>HTTPS/6443, SA Token
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create RBAC resources<br/>HTTPS/6443, SA Token
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create CronJob<br/>HTTPS/6443, SA Token
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Routes (OpenShift)<br/>HTTPS/6443, SA Token
    K8sAPI-->>Operator: Resources created
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Update FeatureStore status
